Text.Value: You've got this backwards. You keep your head, and I pay you nothing.
Get moving. If I see you slavers again, I'll tear you apart.
They belong to the clan. They're coming with us.
Damned right it should.
These shitheads aren't worth the hassle. You got yourself a deal.
Figured you wouldn't.
Read the duergar's mind.
You're no Brithvar. Let me go, and I won't humiliate you in battle. Deal?
Brittle are the foundations upon which the houses of tyrants are built. It seems I judged you to be less brittle than you really are.
You owe - what's the word? Restitution. ([6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Set them free, or I will thrash you like I thrashed Nere.
That wasn't the deal. Zavagh!

EditorData.NodeContext: Zavagh! is a battle cry. za-VAHG!

Text.Value: Here - this should do it. ([6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Yeh might be right about that. The more bodies we got, the slower we move.
Go on, then. Been itching to cut you down a peg.
Some General up there giving the orders, the way Nere told it.
Absolutely not. The gnomes walk free. Right?
Leave.
Whoa. What?! You can't be serious.
Then I'll have to see what price your head fetches. Zavagh!

EditorData.NodeContext: Zavagh! is a battle cry. za-VAHG!

Text.Value: I am freeing these gnomes. Just try and stop me.
I had a deal with Brithvar. You owe me, not the other way around.

EditorData.logicalname: Gave quest to kill eye but player failed

Text.Value: You - you're in my head, aren't you? That ain't right, damn it. Zavagh!
Hah! Did you just roar at me, you freak? Zavagh!
Let the gnomes go. They'll just slow you down.
You got Brithvar chopped - and I still haven't seen a damned coin for my trouble.
Drugnin' Brithvar. I'm lost without him. He'd have this jargh pissin' with fear.
AHH! SHIT! F-fine, I'm not dealing with whatever that was.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He steps back scared at the roar
EditorData.NodeContext: Scared by roar, then a touch embarrassed

Text.Value: You don't need to ask twice, jargh.
Restitution, my arse. You'll find what you need on Nere's corpse.
Place is swarming with Absolute-buggers - a whole army. And I ain't gonna mess about with them.
I can smell your fear so bad I can taste it. Go beg someone else.
That, or - or I add your corpse to the heap. Which is it?
You're afraid, and you should be. Ask for money again, and I'll gut you.
You're free, squatties. Get your legs moving, before I change my damn mind.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to the room in general

Text.Value: Stinking rakkah. If Brithvar was here...
I killed Nere for you. That's payment enough.
Clan's got a cult-army on its hands thanks to you. So pay up. I'll take gold - or your head.
ROAR.
RELEASE THEM, NOW!
You sure they're worth dying over?
Damn right. We'll keep them busy - this isn't their last dig.
Nah. They slow us down, I hold fire to their arses. You should see 'em dance!
The gnomes should be able to go where they please. They are not the duergar's to keep.
You think? I catch so much as a whiff of you, and I'll have you flayed and fried up for dinner.
Shit. That's how it is, eh?

EditorData.NodeContext: Said with a sigh at the beginning.

Text.Value: Hold up, jargh. Y-you ain't just walking away.

EditorData.NodeContext: Aggressive in their words, but something hesitant. They're afraid of you, they just don't want to show it.

Text.Value: Your heart made of stone? They deserved freedom - and you denied it.
Speak up, chief. You can't just let the clan keep them.
It's time I scram, before the buggers at Moonrise charge in.
What makes Moonrise Towers such a threat?
Understood. I won't interfere.
You're mad if you think I owe you a single coin.
Clan, wrap it up. We've scraped this place for all its worth.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.logicalname: at least one other rebel still alive.

Text.Value: Shit - fine. Never could see eye to eye with a clan-sen.
And the slaves? What about them?

EditorData.logicalname: At least one gnome still alive

Text.Value: *You sense hesitation. The duergar talks tough, but fears you.*
They got goblins, drow, gnolls, even humans - ain't no one they won't try to turn. The clans included.
Deal's off, jargh. He told you to squish that floatin' eyeball. Now the damn thing's seen us kill Nere.
I... fine. You ain't worth the trouble anyway.
That so? Then your corpse should be more than willing. Zavagh!

EditorData.NodeContext: Zavagh! is a battle cry. za-VAHG!

Text.Value: Now move out of here - I got shit to be doing.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general.

Text.Value: I - fine. Can't dig for gold when I'm dead, eh?
Good idea. They're a valuable asset.
Don't be ridiculous. I don't have that kind of gold.

Synopsis: In this dialogue, you have killed Nere without doing the duergar mutineers quest. As a result, they want you to pay for the trouble you've caused. You can give them money, persuade them to let you live, or attack.
